OL,3,CMan told police he'll 'miss Grand
OL,4,CTheft Auto' after murdering ex-partner
OL,6,FA man from Oxford who told police he
OL,7,Fwould miss playing the video game
OL,8,FGrand Theft Auto after murdering his
OL,9,Fex-partner has been jailed for life.
OL,11,FRobert Richens, 35, of Luther Street,
OL,12,Fwas given a minimum term of 16 years
OL,13,Fand one month at Oxford Crown Court
OL,14,Ffor the murder of Rachael Vaughan in
OL,15,FMay 2025.
OL,17,FRichens had pleaded guilty to one
OL,18,Fcount of murder at a previous hearing
OL,19,Fon 12 December 2025.
